Multiton Pattern
Definition
Multiton is a design pattern where:
A fixed number of objects are allowed to be created and reused in the application.
It is an extension of:

Singleton → 1 object
Doubleton → 2 objects
Tripleton → 3 objects
Multiton → N objects

Here N can be:
5 objects
10 objects
100 objects
any fixed limit

How Multiton Works
Constructor is made private
Create fixed number of objects
Store them in array/list/map
Return existing objects instead of creating new ones